1 SECTION 4. Section 398-5, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 ”§398-5 Notice. In any case in which the necessity for
4 family leave for purposes of birth or adoption of a child [e^?]£
5 providing care to a child, spouse, reciprocal beneficiary,
6 sibling, or parent; or qualifying military exigency is
7 foreseeable, the employee shall provide the employer with prior
8 notice of the expected birth or adoption serious health
9 condition, or qualifying military exigency in a manner that is
10 reasonable and practicable. Requests for family leave shall
11 include evidence that the employee has submitted the request and
12 provided required data in accordance with section 398-9.5."
13 SECTION 5. Section 398-6, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 "§398-6 Certification. (a) An employer may require that
16 a claim for family leave be supported by written certification.
17 (b) For the birth of a child, certification shall be
18 issued by a health care provider or the family court. For the
19 placement of a child for adoption with the employee,
20 certification shall be issued by a recognized adoption agency,
21 the attorney handling the adoption, or by the individual
