1 officially designated by the birth parent to select and approve
2 the adoptive family.
3 (c) When leave is to care for a child, spouse, reciprocal
4 beneficiary, sibling, grandchild, or parent who has a serious
5 health condition, certification shall be issued by the health
6 care provider of the individual requiring care. Certification
7 shall be considered sufficient if it provides information as
8 required by the director.
9 (d) When leave is for a qualifying military exigency,
10 documentation shall include a copy of official military orders."
11 SECTION 6. Statutory material to be repealed is bracketed
12 and stricken. New statutory material is underscored.
13 SECTION 7. This Act shall take effect on July 1, 2026.
